screenruler
------------------------------------------
ScreenRuler lets you measure objects on your screen using six different 
metrics: pixels, centimeters, inches, picas, points, and as a percentage 
of the ruler's length.

For more information about this package, see the upstream documentation 
in /usr/share/doc/screenruler.

Runtime requirements:
  ruby
  ruby-cairo
  ruby-gconf2
  ruby-gdk_pixbuf2
  ruby-glib2
  ruby-gtk2
  ruby-libglade2

Build requirements:
  cygport-0.9.80-1

License:
  GPL-2+

Canonical homepage:
  http://gnomecoder.wordpress.com/screenruler/

Canonical download:
  https://launchpad.net/screenruler

------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack screenruler-0.891-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport screenruler-0.891-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/screenruler-0.891-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/screenruler-0.891-X.tar.bz2

Or use './screenruler-0.891-X.sh prep' to get a patched source directory

To find out the files included in the binary distribution, you can
use "cygcheck -l PKG", or browse the listing for the appropriate version
at <http://cygwin.com/packages/>.

------------------------------------------

